-- KPI Seeks to Buy Up to 210,000 Tons of Diesel for Italy on Halt
-- B y   L a n a n h   N g u y e n   a n d   R u p e r t   R o w l i n g
-- 2012-04-10T15:08:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/kpi-seeks-to-buy-up-to-210-000-tons-of-diesel-for-italy-on-halt.html
Kuwait Petroleum International
Ltd., a unit of Kuwait Petroleum Corp., is seeking to buy as
much as 210,000 metric tons of ultra-low-sulfur diesel in May
and June in  Europe , according to a company official.  KPI, as the company is known, is tendering to buy four to
seven cargoes of the fuel amid planned maintenance at its
Milazzo refinery on the Italian island of Sicily in May, the
official, who declined to be identified citing company policy,
said today in an e-mailed response.  The tender closes tomorrow, the official said.  Details of the tender are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
